  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Carre
    Class implements the Square shape model A square is a regular quadrilateral, which means that it has four equal sides and four equal angles (90-degree angles, or right angles)
    Factory
    Class that implements the creation of a geometric shape Handles aligned points and points that have the same coordinates
    FactoryPolygonal
    Handles the creation of polygonal shapes
    FactoryQuadrilateral
    Handles the creation of quadrilateral shapes
    FactoryTriangular
    This class handles the creation of triangular shapes
    Figure
    This class implements the most basic shapes, without any condition regarding number of points, lengths
    FigureVide
    Implements an empty shape
    Ligne
    Implements a geometric shape formed by two points This is the so-called segment ;)
    Losange
    Implements a particular quadrilateral shape : A rhombus In Euclidean geometry, a rhombus(â—Š), plural rhombi or rhombuses, is a simple (non-self-intersecting) quadrilateral whose four sides all have the same length.
    Parallelogramme
    In Euclidean geometry, a parallelogram is a (non self-intersecting) quadrilateral with two pairs of parallel sides.
    Polygone
    Implements a polygon shape In elementary geometry, a polygon is a plane figure that is bounded by a finite chain of straight line segments closing in a loop to form a closed chain or circuit.
    PolygoneRegulier
    Implements regular polygons i.e equilateral shapes
    Punct
    Implements a 'Figure' forms by one point
    Quadrilatere
    Implements quadrilateral shapes
    QuadrilatereConvexe
    Implements convex quadrilateral shapes : any line drawn through the polygon (and not tangent to an edge or corner) meets its boundary exactly twice.
    Rectangle
    Implements rectangular shapes A rectangle is any quadrilateral with four right angles.
    Trapeze
    Implements trapezois In Euclidean geometry, a convex quadrilateral with at least one pair of parallel sides is referred to as a trapezoid in American and Canadian English but as a trapezium in English outside North America
    Triangle
    Implements triangular shapes

    TriangleRectangle
